# Working with Us

## Collaborators

We're always interested in hearing from academic, public, and private sector folks who are exploring similar questions. Don't hesitate to reach out over [email](mailto:sciminds@ucsd.edu) if you think there could be exciting opportunities to work together!

## Prospective applicants (all levels)

There are numerous ways to get involved with the lab, but **easiest** way is to [submit this brief general interest form.](https://forms.gle/sySiJmAgMMiqfCTr7) We review responses on a rolling basis and do our best to get back to applicants as opportunities become available that align with your experience & interests.

### Undergraduate 

We ask all students to start as volunteer research-assistants based on your time availability. This way you can comfortably learn the ropes, hone your specific interests, and create opportunities to transition to full-time, independent, and senior thesis positions. Please indicate your interest and availability using the form above.

### Graduate 

**We are not recruiting for the 2026-2027 PhD Cycle.**  
*Please see [UCSD Psychology's prospective student page](https://psychology.ucsd.edu/graduate-program/prospective-students/index.html) for other opportunities in the department.*

